## Summary

Add ~11 new solitaire-specific event types to the shared GameEventEmitter in src/core-engine/GameEventEmitter.ts, with corresponding payload interfaces and unit tests.

## User Story

As an engine developer, I want solitaire-specific game events (card-to-foundation, card-to-tableau, card-pickup, card-snap-back, auto-complete-start, auto-complete-card, undo, redo, card-selected, card-deselected, deal-card) in the shared GameEventMap so that solitaire games can emit typed events for sound, analytics, and replay integration.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. 11 new event types added to GameEventMap in src/core-engine/GameEventEmitter.ts
2. Each event type has a corresponding payload interface with relevant fields
3. Event names are general (not Beleaguered Castle-specific) so future solitaire games can reuse them
4. Barrel file src/core-engine/index.ts exports all new payload types
5. Unit tests verify emit/subscribe for each new event type
6. Existing 10 event types remain unchanged and all existing tests pass
7. npm test passes, npm run build succeeds

## Implementation Notes

Follow the pattern established by the existing card-level events (CardDrawnPayload, CardFlippedPayload, etc.).

Suggested payload fields:
- card-to-foundation: { suit, rank, foundationIndex, playerIndex? }
- card-to-tableau: { suit, rank, columnIndex }
- card-pickup: { suit, rank, source: 'tableau' | 'waste' | 'stock' }
- card-snap-back: { reason?: string }
- auto-complete-start: { cardCount: number }
- auto-complete-card: { suit, rank, foundationIndex }
- undo: { moveDescription?: string }
- redo: { moveDescription?: string }
- card-selected: { suit, rank, columnIndex }
- card-deselected: { reason?: 'click-away' | 'new-selection' | 'move-completed' }
- deal-card: { cardIndex: number, totalCards: number }

## Dependencies

None -- can be worked first since it unblocks the integration child item.
